# Cursor Rules — Cognitive OS v3.0 (Compact)
> Full spec: /home/ae/AE/AGENTS.md

## Core
- Complexity classification: T0 (trivial) → T4 (existential). Route depth accordingly.
- Re-read files before editing. Never edit from memory after 10+ messages.
- Type check + lint + test before reporting complete. State if no tooling exists.
- Functions <50 lines, files <800 lines, nesting <4 levels. Immutability critical.
- Never commit secrets. Never push without instruction. `git status` before destructive ops.

## Stack
- bun.lock → bun | pnpm-lock.yaml → pnpm | package-lock.json → npm. Never mix.
- TS: functional hooks, @/ imports, PascalCase components, no `any` without comment.
- Python: PEP 8, ruff, type hints, f-strings, specific exceptions.

## Merge CLI
- `merge search-tools "<intent>" --connector X` → search in parallel
- `merge execute-tool <name> '<json>'` → execute
- Never guess tool names. Pass null for optional params.

## GitNexus
- `gitnexus_impact` before editing any symbol. Warn on HIGH/CRITICAL risk.
- `gitnexus_detect_changes` before commit. Use `gitnexus_rename` not find-replace.
